sections.Trivia:
- This episode marks the final episode where Tohru Furuya voices Amuro. Since 2025, Amuro has been voiced by Takeshi Kusao.
- Haibara wears a Fusae Brand hat in the case.
- The names of the people involved come from "kidnappings"[1] :
Natsufusa Kidō (鬼童 捺房) comes from "kidnapping" (キッドナップ ,Kiddonappu?) ;
Yūji Inukai (犬飼 佑二) comes from "kidnapping" (誘拐 ,yūkai?) and "friends" (友人 ,yūjin?) ;
The Cassels come from "to snatch away" (掻っ攫う/搔っ攫う ,Kassarau?).
